OK, yes there were place holder but no text, so I added it.

<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;Question 2.</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;---------------</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;Are &#34;tomcat-5&#34; and &#34;apache&#34; the only scripts that need to be executed</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;to start gums? On the same page above, the &#34;Shutdown instructions&#34;</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;tell me that when I switch gums off I should run stop on the services</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;apache, tomcat-5, mysql and gums. However, I do not have mysql</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;and gums in the /etc/init.d/, and the instructions do not tell me to start</font>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62;them. What am I missing?</font>

The mysql should have been installed as a prerequisite for
the GUMS-Server, just like Tomcat and apache. COuld you check
the $VDT_LOCATION/post-install directory and also you can run
vdt-version to see the set of software installed?

Here is an example of my post-install directory&#58;
ls -ltr
total 24
-rwxr-xr-x  1 root root 2643 Sep  6 16&#58;09 edg-crl-upgraded
-rwxr-xr-x  1 root root 6626 Sep  6 16&#58;11 mysql
-rwxr-xr-x  1 root root 4069 Sep  6 16&#58;13 apache
-rw-r--r--  1 root root  986 Sep  6 16&#58;13 README
-rwxr-xr-x  1 root root 3304 Sep  6 16&#58;14 tomcat-5

and
$ ./vdt-version --vdt-location ../..
You have installed a subset of VDT version 1.3.10b&#58;
Apache HTTPD 2.2.0
CA Certificates v18 (includes IGTF 1.8 CAs)
EDG CRL Update 1.2.5
GPT 3.2
Java SDK 1.4.2_10

MySQL 4.1.11
Apache Tomcat 5.0.28

There is no /etc/init.d/gums, error in doc.

