THere is a problem with forward compatibility with the
GUMS client (distributed with 0.4.0) and the GUMS service
(distributed with 0.4.1).  The 0.4.0 version of the GUMS service
has slightly different behavior than the 0.4.1 version (GUMS version
1.1.0 and 1.1.1) but has the same memory leak (which is what
Horst was recalling.)

Are you trying to install this over the top of an existing pacman
installation?  If so could you install in a &#34;clean&#34; directory and
let me know?

Pull newest pacman, unarchive it, source the setup.sh
mkdir /opt/newandfresh
cd /opt/newandfresh
pacman -get  OSG&#58;gums

Thanks-
leigh
