You cannot mix them, and if you can I would upgrade to 0.4.1.

I run GUMS on a dedicated single CPU P4 1U box. GUMS is not resource intensive, but I have found
it best to isolate it from other parts of my infrastructure. As far as Installation I think I use a
straight VDT version rather than anything from the OSG pacman cache.

